{{Wide image|ArgoCrater.jpg|930px|The Martian crater Argo, taken on sol 361 with the left [[navcam]].|45%|right|alt=Black and white image of Martian surface}}

'''Argo''' is a crater in the [[Meridiani Planum]] on [[Mars]], which was visited by the [[Opportunity rover|''Opportunity'' rover]] on approximately its 365th [[Martian sol]]. The crater is about {{Convert|300|m|sp=us}} south of the heat shield and [[Heat Shield Rock]].

