'''Frederick William Rudler''' FGS (8 July 1840, London – 23 January 1915. [[Tatsfield]], [[Surrey]]) was an English mineralogist, geologist, anthropologist, and natural scientist.<ref name=NatureObit>{{cite journal |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=4 February 1915 |title=Obituary: Mr. F. W. Rudler |journal=Nature |volume=94 |issue=2362 |page= 621 |publisher= |doi= |url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015038751858;view=1up;seq=665}}</ref>

After education at the [[Regent Street]] [[University of Westminster|Royal Polytechnic Institution]], Rudler was appointed in 1861 an assistant curator at the [[Museum of Practical Geology]] in [[Jermyn Street]], London and remained in that post until 1876. From 1876 to 1879 he was a lecturer at the [[Aberystwyth University|University College of Wales at Aberystwyth]]. From 1879 until his retirement in 1902, he was the curator and librarian of the Museum of Practical Geology.<ref name=WhoWho>{{cite journal|title='''RUDLER, Frederick William'''|journal=Who's Who|year=1912|page=1856|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015047640092;view=1up;seq=1901}}</ref><ref name=GeoMag>{{cite journal|title=Obituary. Frederick William Rudler|journal=The Geological Magazine|year=1915|volume=52|pages=142–144|url=http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=njp.32101075889996;view=1up;seq=172}}</ref>

Rudler was elected a Fellow of the [[Geological Society]] in 1870 and received the Society's [[Lyell Medal]] in 1903.<ref name=GeoMag/> He was president in 1880 of the anthropological department of the [[British Association]], in 1887–1889 of the [[Geologists' Association]], and in 1898–1899 of the [[Royal Anthropological Institute]].<ref name=WhoWho/> He contributed numerous articles to [[Andrew Ure|Ure]]'s ''Dictionary of Arts, Manufactures, and Mines'' (1875), [[Thomas Edward Thorpe|Thorpe]]'s ''Dictionary of Applied Chemistry'', [[M. M. Pattison Muir|Muir]]'s ''Dictionary of Chemistry'', the [[Encyclopædia Britannica Eleventh Edition|''Encyclopædia Britannica'' (1911)]], and prestigious journals.<ref name=GeoMag/>

==Selected publications==
*with [[George Chisholm (geographer)|George G. Chisholm]]: {{cite book|title=Europe|series=Stanford's Compendium of Geography and Travel, based on [[Friedrich von Hellwald|Hellwald]]'s 'Die Erde und ihre Völker'|year=1885|location=London|publisher=E. Stanford|url=https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/008227497|postscript=; ed. by Sir [[Andrew Ramsay (geologist)|Andrew C. Ramsay]], with ethnological appendix by [[Augustus Henry Keane|A.H. Keane]]}}
