{{Sky|12|26|16.02|+|48|29|36.6}} {{Infobox galaxy | name = I Zw 36 | image = A messy star factory.jpg | image_size = 300px | caption = Blue compact dwarf galaxy known Markarian 209 taken by the [[Hubble Space Telescope]]. | credit = ESA/Hubble & NASA Acknowledgement: Nick Rose | epoch = [[J2000]] | pronounce = | constellation name = [[Canes Venatici (constellation)|Canes Venatici]] | ra = {{RA|12|26|16.02}} <ref name=simbad>{{cite web|title=Search Results for UGCA 281|url=http://simbad.u-strasbg.fr/simbad/sim-id?Ident=UGCA+281|website=Astronomical Data Base|publisher=[[SIMBAD]]|accessdate=15 December 2014}}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|+48|29|36.6}}<ref name=simbad/> | z = 0.000941<ref name=simbad/> | h_radial_v = 282 km/s<ref name=simbad/> | gal_v = | dist_ly = | group_cluster = | type = | mass = | mass_light_ratio = | size = | stars = | appmag_v = | appmag_b = 15.3<ref name=simbad/> | absmag_v = | size_v = | notes = | names = Mrk 209, PG 1223+488, UGCA 281, Z 1223.9+4846, Anon 1223+48, PG 1223+487, UZC J122617.1+482938, [H56] 29, LEDA 40665, SBSG 1223+487, ZW I 36, [M98c] 122350.6+484607, MCG+08-23-035, TC 211, Z 244-18, [MI94] Im 98 | references = }}
'''I Zwicky 36''', often abbreviated to '''I Zw 36''', is a [[blue compact dwarf galaxy]] which is in the [[constellation]] [[Canes Venatici (constellation)|Canes Venatici]]. The dominant population of [[star]]s in I Zw 36 is young in stellar terms, with ages of under 3 million years.<ref>{{cite web|title=A messy star factory|url=http://www.spacetelescope.org/images/potw1450a/|website=www.spacetelescope.org|publisher=ESA/Hubble|accessdate=15 December 2014}}</ref>
